<br>
Lvl 30 warrior w/Jboots &amp; 8 backpacks full of arrows and a bow, running around plinking Mino Hero for 3 hours to kill it = kiting leave him be to kill his uber mob.<br>
<br>
Lvl 60 druid running in circles not damaging lodizal = not kiting, not engaged.<br>
<br>
Lvl 60 druid w/ lodizal persuing and a full guild of people in the zone, buffed and ready to go = pulling, leave them be to kill thier uber mob.<br>
<br>
<br>
Moral of story, if you want to &quot;camp&quot; these uber mobs, do it with sufficient force to drop the mob, in the zone and be ready to pull, when the mob pops.  Otherwise you are just keeping lookout and in a race with everyone else on the server to get the force thier once the mob pops, whether it is chasing you or not.<br>
<br>
I really never understood the logic, I sat here for 2 hours alone waiting for a mob I can not kill, and now that it is chassing me, it is mine.  <br>
<br>
I have the same complaint about Rarefire, people who turn in thier pearl and don't have sufficient force to kill the DRAGON, deserve to lose thier pearl.  This one I think could actully be fixed by verant, all they have to do is simply remove the extra spawn, turn in pearl and boom dragon spawns - could even make the trigger spawn somewhere like the bridge or giant area, so the cleric is not killed right away, but if the dragon is not killed within X amount of time poof - dragon despawns. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ufirbolgnameless.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FirbolgNameless</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 392<br> <font color=#333333>(10/26/01 11:40:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1707.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To the Vision Divine KS's of Lozit</span><hr size=1> Ummm, when you have people in a zone to kill a mob and the druid is waiting for them to get buffed that is called Pulling.<br>
